You’re right — for the **radio button**, keep your existing color variables and make the visible circle larger.

Use this:

```css
.sales-option input[type='radio'] {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;

    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    flex: 0 0 24px;
    margin: 0;

    border: 0;
    background: transparent;
    position: relative;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.sales-option input[type='radio']::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 2px;

    border: 2px solid var(--color-black);
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-white);
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

.sales-option input[type='radio']:checked::before {
    border-color: var(--color-green-dark);
    background-color: var(--color-green-light);
}

.sales-option input[type='radio']:checked::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;

    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);

    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-white);
}
```

This gives:

* `24px × 24px` control
* visible radio about `20px`
* selected fill `var(--color-green-light)`
* dark-green border
* white center dot

Keep your variables unchanged:

```css
:root {
    --color-green-dark: #154734;
    --color-green-hover: #237656;
    --color-green-light: #6BDD00;
    --color-black: #000000;
    --color-white: #ffffff;
}
```

Also remove any older active `:checked::before` or `:checked::after` radio rules, otherwise they may overlap.
